<title>UK: Schroders expands in China.</title>
<headline>Schroders expands in China.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-04-01</dateline>
<text>
<p>British investment bank Schroders Plc said on Tuesday it had opened a group representative office in Beijing as part of an expansion of its presence in China.</p>
<p>Schroders has had an office in Shanghai since 1994 which has grown to a staff of 30.</p>
<p>&quot;The Beijing office will further enhance strong relationships with key government ministries and agencies,&quot; Schroders said in a statement.</p>
<p>It said the office would work closely with Schroders' offices in Hong Kong and Shanghai to assist clients on inward investment and joint ventures in China, on project finance and on capital raising for Chinese companies overseas.</p>
<p>-- London Newsroom +44 171 542 8864.</p>
